President Barack Obama issued a proclamation declaring March 25, 2014, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. The proclamation recognizes the struggle for independence that the people of Greece went through and the contributions of Greek Americans to the United States. It also highlights the historic connection between Greece and the United States, particularly in terms of democratic ideals. The proclamation reaffirms the strong friendship between the two nations and expresses support for Greece as it rebuilds its economy. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.